  "texts": [
    "SSR classified in to (i) Steady state; (ii) Transient state.",
    "Steady stateSelf-excitation is also known as \"steady state SSR\".",
    "Sub-synchronous frequency currents flowing through the generator terminals generate sub-synchronous frequency terminal voltage components.",
    "These voltage components may sustain the currents to produce an effect that is termed self-excitation.",
    "The possibility of the self-excitation of wind power plant (WPP), connected to a series compensated transmission line."
  ]
}